  <h2>Scope</h2>
  <p>This policy applies to <code>himanshuanand.com</code> and its subdomains.</p>

  <h2>Reporting</h2>
  <p>If you discover a security vulnerability, please report it responsibly:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:me@himanshuanand.com">me@himanshuanand.com</a></li>
    <li>Twitter DM: <a href="https://twitter.com/anand_himanshu">@anand_himanshu</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Guidelines</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Do not access or modify other users' data</li>
    <li>Do not perform actions that could harm the availability of the service</li>
    <li>Provide sufficient detail to reproduce the issue</li>
    <li>Allow reasonable time for a fix before public disclosure</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Recognition</h2>
  <p>I appreciate responsible disclosure and will credit researchers (unless they prefer anonymity).</p>

  <h2>Out of Scope</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Rate limiting or brute force on login forms</li>
    <li>Missing security headers on non-sensitive pages</li>
    <li>Social engineering attacks</li>
    <li>Denial of service attacks</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="margin-top:2rem; color:#8892a4; font-family:monospace; font-size:13px;">
